{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":23158,"duration_api_ms":23128,"num_turns":2,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"1e7a6424-75fa-4a43-a598-51010125c0db","total_cost_usd":0.2465255,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":32932,"cache_read_input_tokens":31921,"output_tokens":989,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":32932,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":3,"outputTokens":989,"cacheReadInputTokens":31921,"cacheCreationInputTokens":32932,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2465255,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"rulings":[{"amendment_id":"fr-15-1822a124","decision":"reject","rationale":"Reviewer 2 identifies a critical safety regression that outweighs the observability benefit. After `interrupted_run.take()`, the in-memory state has `active_run = Some(...)`, `interrupted_run = None`, `status = Running`. Persisting this to disk replaces the recoverable on-disk state (`Failed` with `interrupted_run = Some(...)`) with an unrecoverable one (`Running` with `interrupted_run = None`). Since `run resume` explicitly rejects `Running` snapshots (line 1155-1158), a crash after this proposed write but before the stage actually dispatches would leave the project stranded — worse than the current behavior where the stale `Failed` + `interrupted_run` state is fully recoverable. The observability gap (external tools briefly seeing 'Failed' during the retry window) is minor and cosmetic; weakening the crash-resume invariant to fix it is not an acceptable trade-off. If this observability gap must be addressed, it requires a more careful approach (e.g., a dedicated 'Resuming' status or preserving interrupted_run in the written snapshot) rather than a naive write of the current in-memory state."}],"summary":"Rejected the single disputed amendment fr-15-1822a124. While the planner and one reviewer correctly identify the observability inconsistency (on-disk state shows Failed while in-memory state is Running), the second reviewer's counter-argument is decisive: writing the post-take() snapshot would replace a recoverable on-disk state with an unrecoverable one, weakening the crash-resume mechanism to fix a cosmetic issue."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"908e560d-3279-4991-a3e3-bc56751daeef"}
